com.rohanclan.cfml.parser.docitems
Class DocItem

java.lang.Object
  com.rohanclan.cfml.parser.docitems.DocItem
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable
Direct Known Subclasses:
AttributeItem, CFCommentItem, CfmlComment, ScriptItem, SimpleNode, TagItem, TextNode
public abstract class DocItem
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable

The DocItem class is intended to be the abstract base class for parsing and representing internally the structure of a document. It has a name, a item specific name for the item. Examples might be 'cfset' in the case of CFML, or "DoAQuery" in the case of a UDF. DocItem is an abstract class, intended to be the base for representing an in-document item, be it a ScriptItem (like a scripted function) or a CFML tag such as , or CFC stuff (which I'm most interested in!). DocItem stores the name, lineNumber and start & finish offsets within the document so that we can precisely locate it. DocItem also stores the children, therefore it can act as a branch for part of a tree. Hence the addChild() method. Haven't added anything else for retrieving children... because I'm lazy :)

addChild

public boolean addChild(DocItem newItem)
Adds a child to this item's child node list. It first asks the new item whether it's allowed to belong to this item, for example <cfelse> tags must only be a child of an <cfif> tag.

Parameters:
newItem - The new document item to add.
Returns:
true - child added, false - error with child.

insertBefore

public void insertBefore(DocItem newChild,
                         DocItem refChild)
                  throws InvalidChildItemException,
                         NodeNotFound
Inserts the node newChild before existing node refChild. If refChild is null, insert newChild at end of the list of children.

Parameters:
newChild - The new child node to insert
refChild - The reference node, i.e. the node before which the new node must be inserted.
Throws:
InvalidChildItemException - Raised if newChild being added is not valid for this node type.
NodeNotFound - Raised if the refChild node is not found in the node's children.

IsSane

public boolean IsSane()
The final parse check. This is to be run just before the object's parse messages are retrieved. Each document object will run a sanity test to ensure that it is valid. For example a CfmlTagFunction will check to make sure that it has the 'name' attribute.

Returns:
true - item is sane, false - item is not sane.
